A bid by armed hoodlums to attack Dangote Refinery in Lagos has been foiled by security operatives, the police command said yesterday. It said hoodlums numbering about 20 invaded the refinery located at the Lekki Free Trade Zone on Monday through the waters and made to cart away installed armoured cables but were repelled by security operatives guarding the facilitty.   Strike: UNICAL directs students to vacate hostels     2023: TMSH group meets Atiku, Ortom, Ishaku on consensus     2023: Two brothers, ex-Minister pick Ebonyi Gov forms   A statement by spokesman Benjamin Hundeyin said one of the hoodlums was killed during a gun battle, adding that others fled the scene. He said: “One of the hoodlums was hit in the ensuing gunfire and died on the way to the hospital. Investigation has commenced with a view to arresting the fleeing attackers.”